# Rasm C# Production

Read `.claude/skills/coding-csharp/SKILL.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, root `AGENTS.md`, the nearest nested `AGENTS.md`, `docs/usage.md`, and relevant `docs/external-libs/*/rasm.md`.

## Architecture

- Keep one OOP capsule per native boundary, with FP/ROP internals.
- Prefer `Fin<T>`, `Validation<Error,T>`, `Eff<RT,T>`, `Option`, folds, exhaustive switches, and typed failures.
- Use Thinktecture `[Union]`, `[SmartEnum]`, and value objects to collapse sibling types and switches.
- Convert nullable, bool, disposable, command, document, and host-specific effects at the boundary.
- Follow `libs/csharp/AGENTS.md` before new library folders: sibling scan, local API truth, compact roadmap, and value-add above raw native calls.
- Treat `tools/cs-analyzer/Kernel/RuleCatalog.cs` and `CSP####` findings as architecture signals; do not suppress them.

## Do Not Add

- Helper, util, manager, common, options, params, or compatibility-shim files.
- Wrapper-only RhinoCommon, GH2, Eto, LanguageExt, or MathNet renames.
- Domain `try`/`catch`, exception control flow, mutable accumulation, or unbounded primitives where a typed invariant exists.
- `RhinoDoc.ActiveDoc` when a command, UI, or document context already supplies a document.

## Host Baseline

Target RhinoWIP on macOS, GH2, Eto, and app-bundle references from `Directory.Build.props`. Verify risky host APIs with `uv run python -m tools.quality api doctor|xml|types|decompile`.

## Validation

Run `uv run python -m tools.quality static fix [paths...]` after each coherent C# edit batch when safe autofix is desired. Run `uv run python -m tools.quality static build [paths...]` when compile/analyzer proof is needed. Run `full` only when trigger build/config files change.
